modules.description: This module traces HTTP requests and internal spans in a Cohttp Lwt server, integrating with OpenTelemetry. It provides functions to propagate trace context through headers, extract and set tracing scopes, and manage spans with customizable attributes and kinds. Concrete use cases include instrumenting server endpoints for distributed tracing, correlating internal operations with incoming requests, and exporting telemetry data to observability backends.

This module integrates OpenTelemetry tracing with Cohttp Lwt clients and servers, enabling propagation of trace context through HTTP headers and automatic span creation. It works with Cohttp Lwt's client and server interfaces, allowing customization of span attributes and kinds during HTTP transactions. Use it to trace outgoing HTTP requests, correlate client-side operations with server-side traces, and capture detailed telemetry in distributed systems.
